text: The 1984 Davies & Tate British Open Championships was held at Wembley Squash Centre in London from 3–10 April 1984. Jahangir Khan won his third consecutive title defeating Qamar Zaman in the final. Hiddy Jahan represented England from 1984. ==Seeds== ==Draw and results== ===Final=== Jahangir Khan beat Qamar Zaman 9-0 9-3 9-5 ===Section 1=== ===Section 2=== ==References== Category:Men's British Open Squash Championships Men's British Open Championship Men's British Open Squash Championship Men's British Open Squash Men's British Open Squash Championship Category:Squash competitions in London
